# UI Components

The application uses a collection of UI components based on shadcn/ui with Radix UI primitives and styled with TailwindCSS.

## Component Organization

- `/components/ui`: Reusable UI components based on shadcn/ui
- `/components/shared`: Shared components used across multiple sections
- `/components/dashboard`: Dashboard-specific components
- `/components/landing`: Landing page components
- `/components/root`: Root-level components

## Key UI Components

- [components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:components/ui/button.tsx): Button component
- [components/ui/form.tsx](mdc:components/ui/form.tsx): Form components with React Hook Form integration
- [components/ui/dialog.tsx](mdc:components/ui/dialog.tsx): Dialog component
- [components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx](mdc:components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx): Dropdown menu component
- [components/ui/sidebar.tsx](mdc:components/ui/sidebar.tsx): Sidebar navigation component
- [components/ui/table.tsx](mdc:components/ui/table.tsx): Table component
- [components/ui/calendar.tsx](mdc:components/ui/calendar.tsx): Calendar component

## Usage Pattern

The UI components follow a consistent pattern:
1. Import Radix UI primitives
2. Extend with TailwindCSS using class-variance-authority (cva)
3. Export with React.forwardRef for proper ref handling
4. Use with tailwind-merge for class name conflicts
